## Decision-Making Roles and Their Impact on Resource Allocation

Mintzberg’s managerial roles framework identifies four decisional roles relevant to resource allocation:

| Decisional Role    | Description                                                                                  | Relevance to Resource Allocation                             |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Entrepreneur       | Initiates change and innovation to improve organizational processes.                         | Decides on altering resource use to meet evolving needs.    |
| Disturbance Handler| Manages conflicts and unexpected disruptions.                                               | Resolves resource conflicts and reallocates as needed.      |
| Resource Allocator | Determines allocation of money, people, time, and equipment.                                | Directly responsible for resource distribution decisions.   |
| Negotiator         | Engages with stakeholders to negotiate resource commitments and agreements.                 | Secures necessary resources and manages external dependencies.|

These roles are often embodied by the project manager or senior leadership, emphasizing their central role in resource determination ([The-Definition.com, n.d.](https://www.the-definition.com/term/decisional-roles)).

