## Challenges and Considerations in Resource Allocation

- **Preassigned Resources**: Sometimes, team members are preassigned and may lack necessary skills or motivation. Project managers must adapt by providing training or adjusting roles ([Project Risk Coach, n.d.](https://projectriskcoach.com/develop-resource-management-plan/)).
- **Multiple Projects**: Managing resources across concurrent projects requires prioritization and workload balancing to prevent overload ([Quora, 2023](https://www.quora.com/How-would-you-run-a-scrum-team-that-is-handling-multiple-projects-at-the-same-time)).
- **Changing Project Scope**: Resource allocation plans must be flexible to accommodate scope changes and unforeseen delays ([Asana, 2021](https://asana.com/resources/resource-allocation)).

